md.
    In contrast to quantitative scales, which map a continous data domain like time or numbers, ordinal scales map a discrete set of values, like names or categories, to the output range.
    Typical uses for ordinal scales is to map data categories to colors or names to ranges on an x or y axis.

    This page demonstrates the use of ordinal scales with the charts x-axis as well as the category coloring of the bars

    #### Options

    -----

    ##### x-axis

    In this example the state codes are mapped to bands on the x-dimension through an ordinal scale. The ordering of the dimension is by the sequence of values in the data.

button.btn.btn-default(ng-click="shuffleData()") Shuffle x-axis values

