    ##### Color

    Coloring categories is a typical use case for ordinal scales. There are several predefined ordinal scale types that define color sets. The 'plain' ordinal example demonstrates how to define an arbitrary
    set of colors

table.table.table-condensed
    thead
        tr
            th Scope Variable
            th Value
            th Remarks

    tbody
        tr
            td options.colorScaleType
            td
                select(ng-model="options.colorScale")
                    option category10
                    option category20
                    option category20b
                    option category20c
                    option ordinal
            td
                md For details on the pre-defined color scales see [d3 Documentation on categorial colors](https://github.com/mbostock/d3/wiki/Ordinal-Scales#categorical-colors)

        tr(ng-show="options.colorScale=='ordinal'")
            td options.range
            td
                textarea(ng-model="options.colorRange")
            td
                md.
                    List of color values. Colors will be mapped in the sequence of the data values. If there are less range values than categories the colors are reused

                    Please Note: x and y dimensions ignores the range attribute and set it the hight resp. width of the chart container.

